solution: ```class Solution {
    public int[] countBits(int n) {
        int[] ans = new int[n + 1];
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; ++i) {
            ans[i] = ans[i >> 1] + (i & 1);
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses dynamic programming: the bit count of i equals the bit count of i/2 plus the least-significant bit of i. Single pass, no built-ins, minimal arithmetic.

